# Binary files must never be line-ending normalized — EOL conversion rewrites the bytes, which corrupts
# the file and breaks the byte-exact, hash-keyed compiled-type cache (see docs/adr/automation/caching.md).
# The `binary` macro expands to `-text -diff`: no text conversion, no textual diff.
# Verified by automation/Catzc.Base.ModuleSystem/tests/Test-CheckedInBinaries.Tests.ps1.
#
# Only binary types are marked here. There is deliberately NO `* text=auto` rule, so existing text files
# keep their current storage and are not mass-renormalized by adding this file.

# Committed combined C# types assembly — whole directory, any extension, since it is byte-exact build output.
automation/.compiled/** binary

# Binary file types (vendored module assemblies, debug symbols, signatures, native libraries).
*.dll    binary
*.pdb    binary
*.p7s    binary
*.exe    binary
*.so     binary
*.dylib  binary

# C# type sources are the byte-exact key of the compiled-type cache — their combined hash names the committed
# automation/.compiled/Catzc.Types.<hash>.dll. Pin them to LF so every clone/checkout materializes identical
# bytes regardless of core.autocrlf; otherwise a CRLF working tree diverges from the committed build and trips
# the loader's "types changed since they were loaded" guard on re-import. See docs/adr/automation/caching.md.
*.cs     text eol=lf

# Trigger files carry a deployable unit's durable SHA — one 64-hex line + LF, written by Update-Trigger and
# compared byte-for-byte by the trigger-freshness gate. Pin to LF so every checkout materializes exactly the
# bytes the writer produced. See docs/adr/pipelines/durable-sha-globs.md.
.triggers/*.sha256 text eol=lf
